const rawArticleContent = "India’s Autism, ADHD Child development and Mental Health Care Clinic \r\n\r\nWhat is Autism Spectrum Disorder?\r\nAutism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) is a neurodevelopmental Disorder which affects in a way how a child communicates, learns and experiences as well as connects with others in the real world.\r\n\r\nEvery child who experiences ASD symptoms differs in their strengths, needs and challenges.\r\nSome children might have difficulty in communicating their thoughts and feelings  while others may face issues in daily interactions,social gatherings, attention, behavioral challenges and even changing their daily routines. Every kid who has autism might be having or showing different signs and symptoms. This is why it's extremely important to understand every child’s developmental journey individually.\r\n  \r\nParental concern increases when they see few ASD symptoms like the kid doesn’t respond to his/her name, fails to create eye contact, delayed speech, and repeats the same behavioral patterns. In a few cases these changes are visible when their child starts going to school.\r\n\r\n\r\nAt Manovaidya we believe in the philosophy that understanding Autism is much deeper behaviour other than just understanding its basic symptoms or signs. We mainly consider these aspects of developmental processes, ability to communicate their needs effortlessly, emotional well being, learning capabilities and overall growth is totally interconnected to a child's development. With this approach we analyse and provide personalised , purpose driven and meaningful support to every child.\r\n\r\n\r\nHere we ensure that we understand and focus on the overall child development deeply  rather than just addressing the issues and  challenges in isolation.\r\n\r\nWe assure this with the help of comprehensive assessment to understand a child deeply and then create structural guidance. This approach works well with kids and even their family members can gain a better understanding of their child’s strengths, challenges and developmental needs.  \r\n\r\nPeople from different states all across India connect with AUTISM DOCTOR Dr Ankush Garg to get support regarding Autism consultation, ADHD, Mental health and child developmental processes with proper personalised , sensitive, empathetic and structural approach of Neuro Ayurveda Development System.\r\n\r\nMany families especially across India, people staying in Delhi, Ghaziabad, Noida, Greater Noida and different regions of NCR connect with the AUTISM SPECIALIST Dr Ankush Garg to get immense support and appropriate guidance from him related to the matters of Autism, ADHD, Child Development and mental health through personalized and structural approach through Neuro Ayurveda Development System . It is all possible with correct guidance of Dr Ankush Garg  who helps in providing the appropriate AUTISM SUPPORT SERVICES.\r\n\r\nWhat are the early signs of Autism Spectrum Disorder?\r\n\r\nAutism is present differently in each child experiencing it. Autism diagnosis happens to be noticeable either during infancy or during the toddler phase even in early childhood. \r\n\r\nEarly identification can help their parents to understand child needs which would be useful for creating the right environment and Developmental support for children. \r\n\r\nSome of the signs that are commonly observed are:\r\nSpeech Delay in Children, Developmental Delays, Behavioral Challenges, Repetitive behavior patterns, Difficulty in expressing emotions, Repeating the words  frequently , Reduced the use of interactive gestures, Less interaction in social gatherings, Limited responses during conversations, etc.\r\n\r\n\r\nHow does Autism Affect Social Interaction?\r\nReduction of eye contact, Less responsive towards their name, Prefers playing alone, Difficulty in initiating conversations, Reduction in sharing interests and hobbies, Finds difficulty in understanding social cues, challenging communication skills.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat are the Behavioral Challenges associated with autism?\r\n Repetitive body movements and behavioral patterns, Difficulty in changing routines, difficulty in adapting to changes, Emotional regulation is missing if there are any changes in routine.\r\n\r\nHow do sensory processing challenges affect daily life and learning? \r\nKids who have autism experience sensitivity to sound, light and even human touch,  strong reactions towards some colors and even certain foods, uncomfortable in crowds, Emotional responses , have Sensory Processing Issues\r\n\r\nWhat support helps children overcome learning and developmental challenges? \r\nDelayed reaching Developmental Milestones , Difficulty in following instructions, issues in maintaining focus and concentration, Delay in developmental skills, difficulty in social development.\r\n\r\n\r\nIt's always important to remember that only observing one or two symptoms doesn’t mean that the child has ADHD and autism. Every child has their own development concerns which has to be understood in a wider context  to provide the right guidance. Here with the help of Autism Assessment both the doctor and parents can understand the child’s strengths,  Developmental Milestones , challenges and the support they need.\r\nHow is autism understood, diagnosed, and supported in India? \r\nOne of the major concerns amongst parents is the tendency to focus only on the signs and symptoms\r\n\r\nSome of the common parental questions are\r\n\r\nHow can my child's communication skills develop?\r\nWhy does my child avoid social interactions?\r\nWhy is my child so emotional and sensitive?\r\nWhy does my child face difficulty in learning everything?\r\nWhy is he left behind??\r\n\r\nIf we observe all the above questions are essential but focus only on symptoms and not on a deeper level of understanding Child Mental health.\r\n\r\nAt Manovaidya we make sure to provide Proper Parent Guidance For Autism and work together as a team to focus on the real Developmental support for children.\r\n\r\nCommunicating well, learning, adaptable to change , sensory processing, Emotional Regulation, socially interacting are all the aspects that are interconnected to children's developmental needs.\r\n\r\nFor eg difficulty in communication may influence behavioral pattern changes, Sensory issues may result in social interations, even issues in Emotional regulation might cause in family connections, etc.\r\n\r\nThis Child behaviour assessment signifies holistic approach and understanding forms the basic foundation of the Neuro development system followed in Manovaidya. \r\n\r\nRather than viewing the developmental challenges alone we should focus on Family centered autism care to influence overall child development which is beyond all the signs and symptoms.\r\n\r\nEvery child has different Developmental milestones , capabilities, potential as well as understanding. With the right approach of rational thinking , Individualized developmental support, and personalized structural guidance , family support can often develop a path in which Brain Development of children is faster. This overall process helps in developing the right path towards meaningful development of children in the longer run.\r\n\r\nOur Aim at Manovaidya is not only to address individual symptoms improvement but also to support the learning capabilities, emotional regulation, behaviour, confidence as well as overall development in Child’s care in Autism.\r\n\r\n\r\nAutism Assessment  for child developmental approach at Manovaidya \r\nEvery child is special, every child is unique so every developmental journey will be different. One of the most common challenges that families face is comparing their child to the other children of their ages and just looking at the signs as well as symptoms on the internet. Well online sources can increase awareness but can’t help in gaining clarity nor a structural developmental assessment approach on understanding each child individually and deeply.\r\n\r\nAt Manovaidya Developmental delays are dealt with extreme care as we have a procedural Autism Assessment which focuses on understanding overall child developmental profile rather than just evaluating one or two symptoms.\r\nThis assessment process is designed to help families to gain knowledge regarding\r\nCommunication Ability, Social interaction, focus, Learning patterns as well as strengths, Emotional regulation, sensory processing skills, daily routine skills, adapting change, \r\nChild development.\r\n\r\nHere the Doctor's aim is not only to identify the issues or weaknesses but also to understand the child's development overall profile to create the right and structured roadmap for future growth, support and development.\r\n\r\nThis Autism Assessment is considered one of the most important tests to initiate the discussion in order to start the journey of Autism Care In India as this creates the entire profile and provides clarity to both doctors and family. This helps us in creating the right approach for a child's developmental needs and helps in planning appropriate holistic approaches and strategies for the future.\r\n\r\nWhat are the steps to find out if someone has autism?\r\n\r\n\r\nHow can parents help their child with autism and manage daily life? \r\nOnly parents know and understand their child better than anyone else and this is why we at Manovaidya ensure that the procedure starts with detailed understanding of the child's developmental history and entire profile with current concerns and daily routines.\r\n Here we discuss aspects that includes\r\nPregnancy complications and birth history, speech and developmental difficulties, learning abilities, food preferences, eating habits, sleep patterns , behaviour changes, challenges observed repeatedly by parents, etc.\r\nThis information gives the actual picture of an early child developmental journey that helps us in proceeding towards the next steps. \r\n\r\nWhat key factors are considered when creating a child’s behavioral assessment profile? \r\n\r\nAs we know every child develops at their own pace. The major purpose of this Neurodevelopmental assessment is to evaluate and understand the child’s overall profile. It helps in identifying the areas where guidance and therapy can be provided.\r\nThis child behaviour assessment procedure helps us in identifying\r\nCurrent strength areas, Child developmental delays and challenges, areas where additional guidance is needed, adaptability to learn new things, Communication skills, Behavioral challenges, sensory processing issues, etc.\r\n\r\nWhy is a structural Developmental therapy framework so important for Child development?\r\n\r\nOnce the whole Autism screening is done we help in creating the environment that helps in Family-centered autism care . Here at Manovaidya we provide the right structure, individualized developmental support for children.\r\nThis guidance includes proper Parent guidance for autism , Holistic child development planning , Behavioral guidance practice strategies, Appropriate Pediatric developmental assessment to support communication skills, sensory support activities, lifestyle and routine development, and few strategies for assessing real progress.\r\nHere our main intention is to provide families with the appropriate awareness with proper strategies with a structured and holistic roadmap that supports in achieving the right developmental milestones of a child. \r\n\r\nHow does the Integrative Cognitive Development system( Neuro Ayurvedic Development system) help in addressing child development needs?\r\nAt Manovaidya,  Developmental and cognitive behavior concerns are evaluated based on the child behaviour assessment. It is done by Dr Ankush Garg with a proper structured framework through a special approach of the Neuro Ayurveda Development system.\r\n\r\nThere is a proper roadmap designed by doctors to help the families with right awareness, guidance to understand all the interconnected behaviours leading to child development be it learning, communicating, interacting, behavioural patterns and overall child developmental aspects. This Integrative Cognitive Development system not only focuses on identifying the symptoms but also creates a detailed approach of a child's developmental needs through all the above factors. This is all done in a holistic way to create descriptive child development profile\r\nIn order to create the right individualized guidance and recommendations  for child development.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat are the key features of a Brain Nourishment System?\r\nA healthy brain plays the most significant role in paying attention and focusing on the right task, memory, communicating needs, social interactions, etc.\r\nBrain Nourishment system helps in understanding and supporting the strong foundation of integrated healthy cognitive and developmental functioning.\r\nIt influences a few factors such as Attention, learning  curiosity, Communication skills,Cognitive behaviour approach, memory and emotional regulation.\r\n\r\nHow does Gut Response system affect overall health?\r\nIt is proven in various studies that our digestive system not only determines gut but also overall health. Children who experience developmental delays may also ask questions related to  picky eating, digestive issues, even IBS, sensitivity towards certain foods, appetite issues, etc. \r\n\r\nThe Gut Response Systems focuses on understanding how digestive health influences a child's functioning, well being and overall development.\r\n\r\n\r\nHow do Neutral Network systems help in autism?\r\nChild Development occurs through the connections formed in the brain . Here the Neutral Network System helps in proper understanding of how learning attention and communicating  procedures can play a huge difference in underlying developmental pathways. This approach emphasizes a child’s development in key areas such as learning readiness, sensory responses, effective communication, attention skills, and social interaction. These foundational abilities support a child’s overall growth and ability to engage with the world around them. \r\n\r\n\r\nWhat are the signs of sensory processing issues in children?\r\nEach child with autism may experience different signs which include differences in sensory processing. Sensory responses can vary from child to child, affecting how they perceive and respond to sounds, lights, touch, movement, and other sensations in their environment. \r\nHere the sensory integration system helps in understanding and evaluating sensory sensitivities, sensory preferences, regulation, environment, challenges in routines.\r\nWith the right framework doctors can understand the child's needs which can help families in creating a comfortable environment.\r\n\r\nWhat are the key principles of an effective Behaviour Guidance System? \r\nBehavior is one of the most important and integral forms of communication. Children may express their needs , frustrations, discomfort and emotions through their behaviour. \r\nThe main focus of the Behaviour Guidance system is to make families understand the reasons behavior occurs , possible child development assessment behind their behaviour, triggers caused by environment, challenges related to emotions, supportive behaviour guidance approach.\r\n\r\nWhat developmental areas does Manovaidya focus on during autism intervention? \r\nWe at Manovaidya help parents to not only recognize the symptoms but also understand all the aspects related to the child as a whole. Here the process begins with a Neurodevelopmental assessment  that helps in getting clarity on a child's developmental history, communication skills, behaviour patterns, learning and attention needs, sensory responses and parental concerns.\r\nBased on this Child behavior assessment families receive individualistic guidance and a structural approach which will help in evaluating progress on a long term perspective. \r\n\r\nInstead of applying the general approach, Manovaidya follows Individualized developmental support  that helps families in understanding various elements that influences communication, attention, behaviour challenges, emotional well being, and overall development. \r\n\r\nHere our main focus is on providing the suitable support  including Holistic child development, , developmental planning, proper monitoring, long term support, Autism support for parents to move forward with clarity and right direction. At Manovaidya the process begins with descriptive assessment, developmental understanding and one-on-one guidance.\r\n\r\nHow Do We Promote the Development of Children with Autism? \r\n\r\nAt Manovaidya, we follow personalized guidance for every child as each child is unique. Every child has unique interests, abilities, strengths, challenges as well as developmental needs. Our approach focuses on understanding children deeply as a whole, identifying the abilities and interests through Pediatric developmental assessment , recognizing areas where support is needed, providing structured guidance to parents, creating child development support plans, regular monitoring, long term guidance and overall personality development.\r\n\r\nOur main intention is to create a long term sustainable structural approach in order to focus on a child's overall well being rather than adopting a small term symptom solving plan. \r\n\r\nMany families seeking autism management support in India connect with Manovaidya as they are looking for a  tailored approach that focuses on communication, behaviour, social interactions, sensory integration, and all the other aspects which are essential for a child's development.\r\n\r\nWhat role does family support play in autism intervention and child development? \r\nAutism not only affects a child's life but also the siblings, and the entire family environment.\r\nParents may experience numerous challenges such as confusion, anxiety, fear, decision fatigue, emotional exhaustion, stress\r\n\r\nAt Manovaidya parental guidance is considered as the most essential part in the developmental milestone journey. Here we provide immense support on creating awareness on their child's strengths, capabilities, Developmental delays and challenges, communication skills, repetitive behaviour patterns, long run developmental planning. When family members gain clarity they can create an environment and can understand meaningful action which is better for their child's overall well being. \r\n\r\nWhy Do Families Trust Manovaidya for Child Development Support? \r\nSelecting an appropriate support system for a child affected by Autism can often feel complicated and difficult to navigate. Many parents receive recommendations of different professionals. Some may recommend focusing on speech while some on behaviours, sensory integration and daily routines. \r\nMany families explore multiple options just to solve Autism Diagnoses. \r\nAt Manovaidya our aim is to understand not only the child's condition and symptoms but also a deeper analysis of the child's personality in order to provide a tailored development approach. \r\nRather than only focusing on individual symptoms we understand a child though structured Neuro ayurveda development system after proper assessment  brings proper communication , learning, interaction abilities, behaviour, sensory processing, emotional health and overall child development. \r\nThe family chooses Manovaidya due to various reasons. Some of which are:\r\n\r\n-Individualized Understanding of Child Development \r\nEach child is uniquely different. Assessment and intervention are personalized to address each child’s strengths, challenges, and developmental journey. \r\n- Holistic Neuro-Ayurveda Development Framework \r\nThis five-pillar system provides families with a broader understanding of the contributing factors involved in a child’s development, communication, attention, learning, and behaviour.\r\n- Collaborative Family Approach \r\nWe, At Manovaidya believe families should not have to navigate this journey alone. Our guidance equips parents with the understanding and confidence to make informed decisions and support their child's progress. \r\n-Building a Foundation for Lifelong Development \r\nWe believe meaningful development is a long-term journey. Our focus is on promoting steady progress that supports a child’s ongoing growth and development. \r\n-Individualized Support & Progress Tracking \r\nWe provide families with practical recommendations and organized support to help them better understand and monitor their child’s developmental milestones. \r\n-Comprehensive Child Development Support \r\nOur approach may benefit children with difficulties related to communication, behaviour, learning, attention, sensory processing, and social interaction. \r\nFamilies from different states across India choose Manovaidya because they are seeking ADHD and autism support, personalized guidance, and a long-term developmental roadmap for their child. \r\nFamilies from across India, including Delhi, Noida, Greater Noida, Ghaziabad, and the wider NCR region, connect with Manovaidya to access ADHD support, personalized guidance, and a structured long-term developmental plan for their child. \r\nAbout Dr Ankush Garg\r\nChild Development and Mental Health Professional Specializing in Autism and ADHD in India \r\nDr. Ankush Garg is the Founder of Manovaidya and the creator of the Neuro-Ayurveda Development System, an integrated framework focused on delivering tailored support for children and families addressing developmental milestones , behavioural, and mental health challenges. \r\nHis professional work primarily centres on Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD), ADHD, child development, behavioural concerns, speech and communication difficulties, adolescent psychological well-being, adult mental health, women’s emotional wellness, stress management, and mental health care and support for older adults. \r\n\r\nThrough Manovaidya, Dr. Ankush Garg combines the principles of Ayurveda with modern perspectives on brain development, behavioural patterns, emotional wellness, and cognitive health. His approach prioritizes understanding contributing factors,Individualized care approaches , family involvement, and sustainable long-term autism management. By providing detailed evaluations, tailored recommendations, and consistent follow-up care, he enables children, adults, and families to better recognize their concerns and navigate their journey with greater awareness, confidence, and direction. \r\nFamilies across different parts of India approach Dr. Ankush Garg for support related to autism, ADHD, child development, and mental well-being through a thoughtful, personalized, and systematic structural Neuro-Ayurveda framework.\r\nCommonly Asked Questions Regarding Autism \r\nWhat is Autism Spectrum Disorder?\r\nAutism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) is a developmental condition that may impact a person’s communication skills, social skills, behaviours, learning abilities, and sensory experiences. \r\nEvery child with autism has individual characteristics, and their developmental requirements may differ. Some children may encounter difficulties with speech and language development, whereas others may experience behavioral challenges involving social communication, focus and attention, or sensory processing. \r\nAt Manovaidya, autism is not seen as a collection of individual symptoms alone. Rather, it is understood through a complete Neuro developmental assessment that focuses on the child’s communication, behaviour, learning abilities, emotional health, and overall progress. \r\nWhat are the early signs of Autism?\r\nSome early signs of autism can involve lesser eye contact, not responding consistently when called by their name , slower speech or language development, repeated actions, sensitivity to sounds, textures, or other sensations, and social interaction difficulties. Parents may notice differences in how a child plays, expresses themselves, communicates, or reacts to emotions. \r\nEvery child  grows and develops in different ways, so seeing just one or two signs does not automatically mean autism is present. A formal Neuro developmental assessment evaluation can help families recognize a child’s strengths, identify challenges, and understand what support might be helpful. \r\nAt what age can early signs of autism be noticed? \r\nEarly signs of autism may appear during infancy, while others may show clearer signs as they reach the toddler stage or early childhood. Parents may see differences in how their child communicates, makes eye contact, interacts with others, plays, or responds when called by name. Differences in development are visible when the child starts playing with other children or begins school. Identifying these differences early helps families understand their child’s needs and seek the Expert guidance and support in a timely manner. \r\nWhat are the three key signs associated with autism? \r\nWhile every autistic child has individual experiences, common features may include challenges with communication, social interaction differences, and repetitive behaviors or highly focused interests. Parents may notice decreased eye contact, developmental delays, limited participation in social activities, or a strong need for consistency and routines. Some children may also have sensory sensitivities related to noises, lighting, or different textures. Noticing these signs early can help families better understand their child’s needs and prepare for the right support in the future. \r\nWhat are the 7 key indicators of ASD?\r\nCommon ASD symptoms can include less frequent eye contact, delays in speech and language development, limited response when called by name, repetitive actions, challenges with social communication, heightened sensory processing issues, and a strong attachment to familiar routines. However, not every child will experience all of these characteristics, and the level of impact can differ greatly from one child to another.\r\nHow to detect early signs of autism in babies?\r\nSome early signs of autism  in babies may include lesser eye contact, less response to their name, fewer social smiles, limited engagement in interactive play, and differences in speech development. Parents may also observe less frequent use of gestures, such as pointing, waving, or reaching, to communicate interests or engage with others. Since every baby develops at their own individual pace, occasional delays do not necessarily mean a child has autism. However, if child developmental concerns continue, a holistic child development assessment may help better understand the child's communication, social skills, and developmental needs. \r\nWhen should parents be concerned about autism? \r\nParents may wish to seek expert advice if they notice continued difficulties with communication, social interaction difficulties, behaviour, sensory responses, or achieving developmental milestones. Common examples include less frequent eye contact, slower speech development, difficulty responding when called, repetitive behaviors, and trouble connecting with others. Early developmental delays or differences do not always point to autism, but ongoing concerns warrant attention. A developmental review can help families identify whether observed behaviours are within the expected range or whether further help may be needed. \r\nDoes every child with autism experience a delay in speech development? \r\nNo two children with autism are the same, and speech delay is only one possible difference. Some children may have delays in developing language skills, while others may begin speaking at the expected age but struggle with conversation, social communication, or recognizing social signals. The impact of autism differs from child to child, resulting in individual differences in developmental requirements. Understanding a child’s communication skills through a comprehensive assessment helps families discover strengths, recognize difficulties, and implement effective support approaches. \r\nWill my autistic child be able to communicate with words someday?\r\nMany parents wonder if their child will acquire speech and communication skills in the future. Each child with autism follows an individual developmental journey, and communication outcomes vary from one child to another. Some children acquire speech skills at an earlier stage, while others may need extra guidance, support, and time to develop communication abilities. Communication extends beyond spoken words and can include gestures, visual support, social engagement, and various forms of alternative or augmentative communication. With the help of structured guidance ,early understanding, clear guidance, and continuous support can help families encourage communication development based on their child’s individual needs. \r\nCan a child with autism begin speaking after the age of 5? \r\nYes, some children with autism may continue to develop their communication and speech abilities beyond the age of five. Growth does not happen at the same rate for every child, and improvements in communication can continue throughout childhood.There are few factors such as communication skills, adapting changes in routine learning, social interactions, and personalized support may influence child development outcomes. Moving beyond age as the primary factor, it is often more appropriate to assess the child’s complete developmental profile and communication needs. A planned developmental approach can help families find practical ways to improve communication skills and encourage involvement. \r\nCan autism improve over time?\r\nEvery child with autism progresses through development at their own pace. Although autism is a lifelong neurodevelopmental disorder, many children continue to improve and acquire skills in communication, learning, social engagement, and everyday activities as they mature. Child developmental growth can be shaped by factors such as supportive family involvement, educational experiences, progress in communication abilities, and personalized assistance. Rather than focusing only on diagnoses or labels, it is often more helpful to support the child in developing strengths, becoming more independent, and participating in everyday life. Early understanding and steady developmental guidance can help families build a positive plan for the child’s future growth. \r\nCan a child with autism attend a regular school in India? \r\nMany children with ADHD and autism in India study in regular schools, while some may need inclusive classrooms, extra educational support, or learning plans designed to meet their specific needs. The ideal learning environment is determined by the child’s communication abilities, educational needs, social growth, and level of required assistance. Each child has distinct strengths, and school decisions should focus on their personal capabilities and growth needs instead of relying solely on autism diagnosis. A systematic child developmental assessment can provide parents with a clearer understanding of the educational environment most suited to their child’s learning needs and development. \r\nHow can parents support a child with autism at home? \r\nParents play a fundamental part in shaping a child's development. Simple approaches such as establishing regular routines, promoting communication, offering organized learning activities, encouraging social engagement, and creating a peaceful environment may help children take part more effectively in everyday activities. It's very much essential for parents to acknowledge their child’s strengths rather than flaws. Consistent small steps, taken over time, can bring meaningful growth. At Manovaidya, guiding parents is an essential part of empowering families to better understand and nurture their child’s development. \r\nWhat is the Neuro Ayurveda development system?\r\nThe Neuro-Ayurveda Development System is a systematic model designed by Dr. Ankush Garg to guide families in understanding developmental, behavioural, and psychological wellness needs. The system focuses on five connected areas: Brain Development Support, Gut Function System, Neural Connection Network, Sensory Processing System, and Behaviour Management System. Moving beyond a focus on separate symptoms, the framework encourages a wider perspective on communication, learning, behaviour, attention, sensory processing experiences, and overall growth. This structured method enables families to gain deeper insight into child developmental requirements and future support planning. \r\nHow does Manovaidya conduct assessments and provide support for children with autism? \r\nAt Manovaidya, autism assessment aims to understand the child as a whole, rather than focusing on individual symptoms separately. The process may cover developmental milestones, communication skills, learning approaches, behaviour, sensory experiences, and concerns shared by parents.This approach enables families to access personalized support and a structured plan to guide development. Support helps families gain insight into communication, behaviour, learning, sensory integration, and holistic child development through the Neuro-Ayurveda Development System. The intention is to provide tailored guidance, consistent support, and developmental strategies that foster the child’s long-term growth. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSchedule a consultation \r\nIf you are looking for guidance on autism treatment in India, autism assessment, child development support, or concerns related to communication, behavior, learning, and developmental challenges, you can schedule a consultation with Dr. Ankush Garg and the Manovaidya team. Through a detailed evaluation and personalized support plan, families can better understand their child’s unique developmental needs and discover the right steps to encourage progress, learning, and overall health.\r\nStart the Journey to Better Development \r\n-Autism Evaluation\r\n-Individualized Growth Guidance\r\n-Parent & Family Assistance & Support\r\n-Neuro-Ayurveda Development Approach\r\n-Personalized Progress Roadmap \r\nManovaidya Clinic\r\nNoida, Uttar Pradesh, India \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";

